Unless the child is subject to trial as an adult, if the child is not released, the peace officer shall contact the court-designated worker who may:
Release the child to his parents;
Release the child to such other persons or organizations as are authorized by law;
Release the child to either of the above subject to stated conditions; or
Except as provided in subsection (7) of this section, authorize the peace officer to retain custody of the child for an additional period not to exceed twelve (12) hours during which the peace officer may transport the child to a secure juvenile detention facility or a nonsecure facility. If the child is retained in custody, the court-designated worker shall give notice to the child's parents or person exercising custodial control or supervision of the fact that the child is being retained in custody.
